03/10/2010
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The inauguration of Patriarch Irinej as head of the Serbian Orthodox church is taking place on Sunday (October 3rd) in the Pec patriarchy.
Representatives of Orthodox churches and other religious communities are attending the enthronement ceremony.
Several thousands of believers are expected to attend the event.
Serbia will be represented by President Boris Tadic.
KFOR says has it taken all necessary security measures, in co-operation with the Kosovo Police and EULEX.
(Beta, RTS, Tanjug, B92 - 03/10/10)
